## resets

Property name: `resets`

Value type: `<prop-encoded-array>` encoded as a list of phandle + reset-specifier pairs

A list of reset input signals as specified by bindings of the reset provider.

---

**From binding** (\`qcom,pcie-sm8550\`):\n\nphandles to the reset lines for both SATA bridges

---

**Source:** Linux kernel Documentation\n\n```\n- resets: phandle to the relevant PMB controller, one integer indicating the internal
  bus number, and a second integer indicating the address of the CPU in the PMB
  internal bus number.

Example:

	cpus {
		cpu@0 {
			compatible = "arm,cortex-a9";
			reg = <0>;
			...
			enable-method = "brcm,bcm63138";
		};\n```
